I highly recommend this place to anyone that loves the sound of the ocean. The waves crashing against the jetty along with the sound of the seabirds is so relaxing. The fog rolls in so fast that the city disappears right before your eyes. It must be very popular with the locals. I could get use to taking early morning or evening walks with the puppies out here.<//Review>

It's an okay place to stop by. It's a run down town and the sewage place is near by the lighthouse, sending a smell that you don't want to remember every 5 seconds. The bathrooms by the beach is not clean at all. I only gave it a 2 star because of the lighthouse and because I witness a humpback whale that day. Oh,  there is a little carnival near by. I didn't check it out, but if you have kids or to have a good time, that could be place to stop by.<//Text>

I was unable to hear the employee through the drive through speaker so I kept having to ask her to repeat what she was saying. Every time I come in, the staff acts like I'm a bum getting ready to steal something. They're selection is super limited and overpriced though very well kept. Today I asked if they had pipe tobacco and was told to check out 7/11. When I pointed out that that was like asking for a quality cigar and being handed a swisher, the gentleman offered a half hearted recommendation for Mission Pipe. Mission is an excellent shop, but 10 miles away from where I was, through rush hour. Plus, there are other shops closer. Unless you are desperate, go to any other cigar shop in the south bay. Club Havana is nearby in El Paseo, great staff, okay selection of pipe smoke, excellent cigar selection; Campbell Cigars in Bascom and Union has both pipe and cigars, the guy really knows his cigars. Smaller selection than others, but good prices and good condition; the aforementioned Mission Pipe, massive selection of cigars, plus a great array of pipe tobacco, plus a staff who knows.more about pipe and tobacco than you'd think possible; and West Cost off Almaden and 87, with an incredible cigar section and big pipe tobacco inventory. Know their cigars really well, a little more limited on the pipe knowledge.

Best part of all of those places: none of them treat you like garbage who you need to get out of your store asap. Save your money and avoid these snobs.<//review></record></dataset><record>

3< /rating>
<review>The cigar selection is pretty strong. Nothing compared to Mission Pipe Shop (maybe 1/3 of Mission Pipe). Most recognizable brands would be Padron, LFD, My Fathers, CAO(I think), Arturo Fuente, higher end Diamond Crowns, but no Davidoff, however - just FYI.
I rate two stars because the lounge itself, is awkwardly situated. There wasn't seating that offered any type of privacy - especially for conversations. There was one employee there that didn't come across very friendly, and was going through the motions of trying to sell a stick. The other employees I met were great! If a place wanted to get extra money for a lounge fee out of me, it strictly comes down to the atmosphere, and that wasn't there for me, unfortunately.

Might be going back because of their solid range of selections with Padron and My Fathers, but won't be staying much longer than that.<//review>< Pictures>

<Text>As someone who travels, I have been to my fair share of Denny's.  This one is definitely low on totem pole of decent Denny's:

!) There is HUGE sign that says free wi-fi; a good thing in an area that get's spotty reception for my cell network.  Go inside.  No Denny's wi-fi shows on my phone.  The waitress says "Yeah!  It hasn't worked for a really long time. We should take that sign down."  Forgivable, but still not a good way to start off.
2) The ATM is out of order.  Not fantastic in an area where the nearest bank is over 30 minutes away.
3)  Tiny restroom.  One urinal, one stall.  What?!?!  The only reason this Denny's exists is because of travellers on I-5.  You should expect that people are coming in with full bladders and bowels.  Every other Denny's I've been, even the one down the street from my house in urban L.A., has at least twice that number.  The place seats over 150 according to their maximum occupancy sign.
4)  4 seats at the counter.  Again, your whole reason for existence is to get travellers in and out so they can continue their trip.  Poor design to meet the need of the single traveller who just wants a place to sit, refuel, and get back on the road without having to wait for a table.
5) Bugs.  An earwig ran across the table during my meal.  Final straw leading to low rating.

The staff was nice enough, the food decent, but I recommend driving on to the next Denny's or eating at one of the fast food places in Buttonwillow if you are really hungry.< /Text>< user>

Re:  Our visit to Denny's Buttonwillow for lunch at 12:30 p. m. on Wednesday, Dec. 29, 21105:

{We do  not travel as much as we used to, but Denny's is still our restaurant of choice.}

Last Wednesday, the waitress brought our water and said she would return shortly for our orders....She came back in 10+ minutes.

Five+ minutes later, our waitress stopped by and said, "Your food swill be here in LESS than five minutes. .... I checked my watch.....9 1/2 minutes later our food came.....{My wife had just said, "Let's go somewhere else.

We ordered Tilapia.  The waitress did not tell us that soup or salad came with the meal.

The Tilapia was NOT grilled....It was pan fried and greasy.

The vegetables were  NOT steamed....They were sauteed.

The toasted bread was hard and dry.

It was an "OVER-ALL-UNPLEASANT EXPERIENCE!"

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

At 8:00 p. m. we stopped at the Denny's an Avenida de Pico for our eveninvg meal.   My wife had the
Tilapia again.  The meal was superb...Thanks.

Sincerely, Larry D. Flora  (1219 E. Barham Dr. Space 8, San Marcos, CA 92078)</review>

<rate>5<//rate>< text>
We had never been to San Francisco before and had a few hour layover, during which our local friend brought us here saying it was the best bar in the city. We couldnt have agreed more. Friendly/ helpful service, clean bathrooms, delish cocktails (REAL ones. Maybe not to the extent of having egg whites on hand to make a Fizz [that actually made it better/ more local feeling], but she was the first bartender we ran into outside of Vegas or New York that could easily make a Penicillin no questions asked), awesome snack bowls (needed after a couple cocktails before heading back to the airport), and fun atmosphere.< /text>

< Text>
This is, and has been for over a decade, my favorite neighborhood bar. It's best when it's not elbow-to-elbow, which can happen at peak times on the weekends, but the unbearable crowdedness typically doesn't last too long because it's hard to enjoy yourself if you're not seated; almost every square inch of the place is occupied by tables with white tablecloths and candles. And the CRT television playing some classic black-and-white movie or another completes the scene.<//Text>

<Rating>5</Rating>< Text>
The restaurant is great - ambience, staff, food, price - a good experience all in all! We visited during the Covid-19 pandemic. The outdoor dining tables have sufficient space between them. We ordered spaghetti with marinara sauce & sweet-sour chicken. The food was very flavorful & generous portion size. It's the closest restaurant outside the Kings Canyon national park (Grant Grove side). The area is dotted with succulents in cute pots, also has well-mannered cat & dog.< /Text>

< review>
We booked through Airbnb for two nights while we visited Sequoia and King's Canyon. Ended up cancelling halfway through and staying only one of the two nights because:
- The room smelled really badly of cats, and we had to buy a thing of Febreze just to cover it up.
- The hot water in the sink wasn't working properly (spitting and sputtering and not putting out hot water), so we didn't even try the shower.
- The mattress was probably the hardest mattress we've ever slept on.
- Walls were thin so you could hear the cats outside and neighbors next door.
- Check-in was a little disorganized.
